answerText: John Ashbery[10] John Ashbery, along with other poets like Frank O'Hara and Kenneth Koch, was part of a school of poetry centered in this city. Langston Hughes and Countee Cullen were members of the Harlem Renaissance, a cultural movement in this city.

question: Question:  [10] Name this poet of the Henry Darger inspired Girls on the Run, who described an object which shows an "image / Glazed, embalmed, projected at a 180-degree angle" in another poem.
